│ THOUGHT: The issue is likely that when both incoming values to a recurrence │
│ phi are identical, the vectorizer should recognize this and handle it       │
│ specially to avoid creating unnecessary broadcast operations that cause     │
│ dominance issues. Let me look at how the vectorizer determines if something │
│ is a recurrence.                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the test case again:                                             │
│ - `%for = phi i8 [ %for.start, %entry ], [ %for.next, %loop ]`              │
│ - `%for.next = and i8 %for.start, -1` which is equivalent to `%for.start`   │
│                                                                             │
│ So effectively, `%for = phi i8 [ %for.start, %entry ], [ %for.start, %loop  │
│ ]`                                                                          │
│                                                                             │
│ This means the phi node always has the same value regardless of the path    │
│ taken. In such cases, the phi node could be simplified to just use          │
│ `%for.start` directly, but the vectorizer needs to handle this case         │
│ properly.                                                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ The problem occurs during vectorization when the vectorizer tries to create │
